'''Periodic short-interval diffuse discharges''' are a type of [[EEG]] abnormality with periodicity less than 4.0 seconds.<ref name="pmid12967574">{{cite journal |last1=Yemisci |first1=M |last2=Gurer |first2=G |last3=Saygi |first3=S |last4=Ciger |first4=A |title=Generalised periodic epileptiform discharges: clinical features, neuroradiological evaluation and prognosis in 37 adult patients. |journal=Seizure |date=October 2003 |volume=12 |issue=7 |pages=465-72 |pmid=12967574}}</ref> They can consist of sharp waves or spikes, spike and wave, polyspikes or triphasics with background attenuation in between transients.<ref name="pmid12967574" />

